The paper discusses propositional logic programs and the stable model semantics, which are commonly used in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and logic (cs.LO) research. The focus on extending the rules to make programs more concise suggests a focus on programming languages and compilers (cs.PL). The decision procedure mentioned in the abstract suggests a focus on algorithms and data structures (cs.DS), while the practical applications of the stable model semantics suggest a focus on software engineering (cs.SE).
